<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="43.[151,1436,360,889]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,793,817]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="H. Milne Edwards" baseAuthorityYear="1834" box="[322,536,793,817]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Leptodius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exaratus">
<emphasis box="[322,536,793,817]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Leptodius exaratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the most common brachyuran species found on intertidal rocky shores along the Persian 
<collectingRegion box="[352,403,829,853]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="Gulf" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Gulf</collectingRegion>
coast. This species shows a wide variability of colour patterns. The first male gonopod is a good and constant character for the identification of this species.
</paragraph>
